                {
                  "uid": "6c2f5dc2-86c5-42d3-8bc5-a8d06691784a",
                  "componentName": "Quote",
                  "dataSource": "{05F43213-86B2-4A22-AE98-0619126E4BD5}",
                  "params": {},
                  "fields": {
                    "blackBackground": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "text": {
                      "value": "In 2019, under the banner of a Perpetual Planet,  Rolex is joining forces with key individuals and organizations to help find SOLUTIONS TO ENVIRONMENTAL CHALLENGES. "
                    },
                    "author": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "isQuote": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "rightDirection": {
                      "value": true
                    }
                  }
                },
                {
                  "uid": "96ab6fd4-b344-4de0-8f72-7cda5e1aa2c0",
                  "componentName": "SimpleText",
                  "dataSource": "{50EBA46A-8887-4D33-96D7-82D9FAB34E2B}",
                  "params": {},
                  "fields": {
                    "noMargin": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "borderTop": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "isBold": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "lettrine": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "title": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "titleColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "text": {
                      "value": "With Dr Earle as the chair of our Editorial Board here at Ocean Geographic Magazine, it is our constant privilege to be guided by her wisdom and insight. We have also been extremely fortunate to have Dr Earle as the Chief Scientist on all three of our Elysium Expeditions to the Antarctic, Arctic, and Coral Triangle over the past decade. We are now working with Dr Earle to support Deep Hope, a California-based, non-profit initiative with the vision of building submersibles that will open up access to our deep seas.\n<br/><br/>\n\nThe Deep Hope subs will be the tools to connect our uninformed present with an enlightened future that properly values its oceans. As Sylvia always says, “Onwards and downwards!” \n<br/><br/>\n\nMany organizations work to forward the ideals espoused by Sylvia Earle, but her oldest and most unwavering supporter is Rolex.  In 1979, Earle set the world untethered diving record, descending 381 metres (1,250 feet) beneath the surface of the Pacific Ocean in a pressure-resistant JIM diving suit. Soon after that, she became a Rolex Testimonee, and has been their premiere ocean ambassador ever since. \n\n"
                    },
                    "textColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "usText": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
