                    "lettrine": {
                      "value": false
                    },
                    "title": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "titleColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
                    "text": {
                      "value": "Since 2010, through her Mission Blue initiative, Earle has inspired communities and governments to shield marine life that is at risk from human pressures through Marine Protected Areas (MPAs) she calls Hope Spots. These are areas of the oceans designated as being vital to the preservation of species, from the range of diversity a particular site displays or its significance as a home to endemic, rare or endangered species, or places where local communities rely on a healthy marine environment for their survival.  With the support of Rolex, the number of Hope Spots has increased from 50 to 112 over the past five years. Earle aims to protect 30% of the world’s oceans by 2030. Currently, only 8% of the oceans have some form protectionbut only 3% percent are accorded full protection.\n <br/><br/>\n\nFor nearly a century, Rolex has been an active supporter of pioneering explorers, individuals who have pushed back the boundaries of human endeavour by venturing to the most extreme places on Earth to shed light on the natural world.\n\n\n\n"
                    },
                    "textColor": {
                      "value": ""
                    },
